<paragraph blockId="24.[164,779,809,1902]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis box="[164,300,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Description:</emphasis>
Entirely chestnut brown; head, pronotum, and all sternites apparently darker than the elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[164,779,809,1902]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Supraorbital sulcus distinct. Third antennomere shorter than fourth; fifth subequal to or slightly longer than fourth; sixth shorter than fifth; seventh subequal to fifth; eighth to ninth each slightly shorter than preceding one; tenth subequal to or shorter than ninth; last subequal to first; distal three to four antennomeres thickened or not; the antennae extend well beyond half of the elytra over the pronotum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[164,779,809,1902]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Pronotum with antebasal transverse impression, and with punctures in the antebasal transverse impression stronger than those on the rest of the pronotum. Apex of prosternal intercoxal process convex, with preapical depressions. Prosternal intercoxal process 1.4 times wider than the distance between the anterior margin of the prosternum and the coxal cavity; distance from the anterior margin of the prosternum to the end of the intercoxal prosternal process 3.3 times the minimum width of the prosternal intercoxal process.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[164,779,809,1902]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Scutellum as broad as long, apex acute. Mesosternum depressed on top, with concave posterior margin. Elytra with maximum width at posterior two-fifths. Elytral apex convex, and broad. Elytral punctures do not form rows, and are moderately strong, with the distance between adjacent punctures 1–3 times the diameter of a puncture in the anterior half of the elytron. First metatarsomere distinctly longer than half of the metatibia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[164,779,809,1902]" lastBlockId="24.[826,1441,198,740]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
Subparallel ridges on the first abdominal ventrite do not reach the middle of the ventrite, and converge distally (
<figureCitation box="[267,349,1849,1872]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
). Last visible tergite of females with a shallow groove. Lobe in the middle of the posterior margin of the last male ventrite with convex posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[927,1008,228,251]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[826,1441,198,740]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
Aedeagus gently curved in lateral view, with acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[895,976,290,312]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, ventral surface convex, with a transparent window, apex obtuse, with a tiny denticle in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1192,351,373]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
); distal opening partially covered with lamina (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1234,381,404]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
). Arms of tegmen shorter than stem (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1136,412,434]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[826,1441,198,740]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
Spermatheca with horizontal part of pump longer than vertical part, receptacle about three times longer than wide, outer side convex, inner side indistinctly concave in middle, not narrowing towards duct; duct twisted several times (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1185,565,587]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Vaginal palpus distinctly narrowed at distal two-thirds; lateral unsclerotized area shorter than distal or proximal sclerotization; proximal sclerotization longer than distal sclerotization (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1154,687,710]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
). Distal sclerotization of tignum longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1215,718,740]" captionStart="Figures 90–98" captionStartId="25.[144,234,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[308,1260,415,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-96@25.[303,1263,412,1794]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 90–98. Tegyrius pucetibialis sp. nov.: 90, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 91, male last abdominal ventrite; 92, aedeagus, ventral view; 93, aedeagus, lateral view; 94, distal opening; 95, tegmen; 96, spermatheca; 97, vaginal palpi; 98, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443642/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[826,1442,810,985]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis box="[826,1061,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Sexual dimorphism:</emphasis>
First pro- and mesotarsomeres slightly enlarged in males compared with females. Mesotibia in lateral view distinctly curved and distally enlarged in males, slightly curved and distally not enlarged in females. First metatarsomere of male unmodified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[826,1441,1054,1383]" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis box="[826,1094,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="350">Measurements (n = 4):</emphasis>
