<paragraph blockId="25.[144,759,198,281]" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis box="[144,337,198,220]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">Etymology: Puce</emphasis>
means ‘flea’ (coloured) in French. The name refers to the brown colour of the beetle, and the modified mesotibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[144,759,320,373]" lastBlockId="26.[164,779,198,556]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="352" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis box="[144,498,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[261,498,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pucetibialis" status="sp. nov.">Tegyrius pucetibialis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[507,595,321,342]" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is confined to the upper reaches of the Nilgiri mountains. It can be separated from the closely related 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[1210,1380,198,220]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1210,1380,198,220]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">T. nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="25" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by colour, and by the structure of the aedeagus. The general colour of 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[1056,1216,259,281]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pucetibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1216,259,281]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">T. pucetibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1224,1309,260,281]" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is brown, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[997,1167,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[997,1167,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">T. nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1177,1264,290,311]" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is black. The apex of the aedeagus in ventral view is unidentate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[846,1015,351,373]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pucetibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[846,1015,351,373]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="351">T. pucetibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1032,1129,351,372]" pageId="25" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, whereas it is bifid in 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[164,335,198,220]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,335,198,220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="352">T. nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[344,432,198,219]" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Although both of them share the same host plant, they are not sympatric, as 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="352">T. nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[313,401,260,281]" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is confined to the lower reaches of the Nilgiri Hills. 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[425,668,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pucetibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[425,668,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="352">Tegyrius pucetibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[685,779,290,311]" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[386,563,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[386,563,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="352">T. nigrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[580,674,321,342]" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having sexually dimorphic mesotibia, a broad elytral apex, the same host plant, and a narrow and close, but parapatric, range of distribution. The two species can be separated from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[682,778,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[682,778,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="352">Tegyrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the sexually dimorphic mesotibiae and the structure of the aedeagus, besides the broad elytral apex.
</paragraph>
